HEADWORD: Impersuasible
<hw>Im`per*sua"si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>persuasible</ets>: cf. OF.
<ets>impersuasible</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not persuasible; not to be moved
by persuasion; inflexible; impersuadable.</def> <au>Dr. H. More.</au> --
